stylometry: The concept of a logical upper limit is to know what the maximum number of something that you can produce and that there is a limit and you cant exceed that amount.  For example with the fixed cost model about the machines we did in class, there was a logical upper limit to how many machines each plant could produce.  We used the 0-1 interger, 0 meaning we were not going to produce any, and 1 meaning we were going to produce the machines.  If there was a 1, then we could produce the maximum number of machines in that plant that the logical upper limit allows us to produce.
